SIMPLE: hand-me-down
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hand-me-down
<hw>hand-me-down</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>obtained or used
after prior use by another person.</def> <note>the term
<ex>hand-me-down</ex> is often used of clothing previously worn by older
family members. The term may also be used metaphorically of
ideas.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hand-down, secondhand, used.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hand-me-down</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: hand-me-down
<hw>hand-me-down</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An outgrown garment given to
one person after use by another; -- usually transferred between members
of a family or close friends; <as>as, because she was the youngest of
four girls, the clothes she wore were always
<ex>hand-me-downs</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>handoff</ent>⟦br⟧
